            I was grateful to the hon. Member for Meriden for mentioning the Secretary of State's response. On the Floor of the House, he told me that local matters must be decided by local opinion. I ask that that be the case, without pressure from the Department of Health and its Ministers. Makers of local opinion&#x2014;that must include citizens as well as members of the professions&#x2014;should be given freedom.
          </p>
